(in order of appearance from song starting (aka not including their awesome intro):
Joshua (Hong Jisoo ğŸ¦ŒorğŸ°) 0:42 - center, lead vocalist, a sunday morning latte of confidence and assurance
Hoshi (Kwon Soonyoung ğŸ¯) 0:56  - lead dancer and leader of performance unit, obsessed with tigers forever pure
Woozi (Lee Jihoon ğŸš ) 1:06 - trifecta of perfection aka producer of 99% of their songs, buff king, leader of vocal unit
Wonwoo (Jeon Wonwoo ğŸ˜¼) 1:15 - lead rapper, a perfect snack of calm and wit
Mingyu (Kim Mingyu ğŸ¶ ) 1:20 - lead rapper, puppy dog eyes and brand ambassador for everything luxurious
DK or Dokyeom (Lee Seokmin âš”) 1:26 - lead vocal, eternal sunshine and lover of the small things in life
Seungkwan (Boo Seungkwan ğŸŠ) 1:36 - lead vocal, baby of Jeju and literally the entertainment industry's blessing
S.Coups (Choi Seungcheol ğŸ’) 1:43 - SVT and carat's leader, lead rapper, competition's  biggest threat and struggler of realizing just how wonderful he is
Dino (Lee Chan ğŸ¦•) 1:49 -  maknae, lead dancer who thrives off bettering himself and understanding those around him, the least maknae of maknaes ever
Jeonghan (Yoon Jeonghan ğŸ‘¼ ) 1:56 - lead vocalist, angel with a dual edge sword (loves being competitive and joking around with members)
The8 (Xu Minghao ğŸ¸) 1:59 - lead dancer, assertively chic and forever at peace... his self confidence and assurance forever astounds us
Jun (Moon Junhui ğŸ˜º) 2:16 - lead dancer, funniest despite being one of the quietest of group, quick in wit but permanently perplexed trying to understand those around him
Vernon (Chwe Hansol ğŸ¸orğŸ¤˜) 2:28 - lead rapper, co-producer of many songs, introverted music geek with a profound outlook on life, responsible and so very loveable

Good day, Carats! Please, letâ€™s stream SEVENTEENâ€™s mvs! We are literally a big fandom, but why doesnâ€™t we use this power to give back and help SEVENTEEN?

author: @alex-fs9yt
text: This video is shockingly underrated. How can it have only 4.1M views in three months when Ready to Love has 43M views in four months? Even Hoshi and The8's solo tracks have more views than this video, where all members participatd. I know this is labelled a "special video", but why isn't it included in the channel's official music video playlist? It really deserves to be. It may have been filmed all in one place but that shouldn't make it any less of an MV. The song is so good, I can't believe more people haven't heard it. And have you seen the visuals, camera work and choreography?? This definitely serves more views. In my opinion this is one of the best things that happened this year.

text:
I got an F1 2020 ad right after this video which is amusing but more importantly

after watching a bunch of GoSe and silly VLive clips form SVT sometimes I forget that beyond being charismatic comedic and charming in personality they're also fucking phenomenal dancers
like the 95 line will call themselves lazy but that's impossible given how much practice and effort and work goes into getting choreo like this right

The formations are so good, I love how the focus of each line flows so naturally into their center position. Obviously it's one of their most recognized strengths but my God the synchronization. It's incredible that thirteen people of different builds, different heights, can move as one in such a pleasing way to the eye.

Also the visuals hot damn literally everyone looks fine as hell in this

You got the choreography totally on point. From the all looking good as a group, to the individual minutiae. I love the consistency with your mv's. This track sounds like the summer sunshine gets hotter listening to this. It hit the adrenal glands and excites them beautifully. Brilliant how the Group allow each other's unique vocal range talents exude. As a slight constructive criticism (though I do make this point quite often with various groups), maybe be mindful of the synthesised unison of vocals on the tracks. It does help the polished professional sound, from a Production Team viewpoint, yet the fans love being able to see the Group's development, evolving, improving, learning how to capture our love & our appreciation in the various possibilities with musical arrangements, the songs themselves, the mv's & the complete conceptual profiling as the Group progresses into each new era. Growing with a Group allows the fans' to learn how to appreciate each talented aspect more. Growing up with a favorite Group, enjoying the developments & evolving with the Group(s) is part of the brand marketing that SVT have really got good control of. Fans consistently expect & receive excellent enjoyable entertainment. Maybe be careful that SVT as a Group doesn't loose the ability to input all that individualism that you harness together. Synthesised voices have a tendency to put the control of progress onto the technical staff, who are important yet are not who the fans want to see. Younger generation fans globally may not remember the synthesised songs fading away to non popular. They typically have a 'chosen few' fan base. Look at how the major global artists let their work, their image, & talents, including vocal range, evolve with them & their progress. Even the popularity of genres such as techno, house & garage have peaked & troughed from the use of synthesis. Our human ear gets tired of the humming buzzy sound of synth'd vocals & music. That's part of the evolution of technology. It can't  be human. Natural human evolution is a winning trait that fans understand & relate to. Our listening ears thrive more from human voice, then the fans always remember whose efforts made them feel that much better. ğŸ‘„ğŸ˜

author: @mdrdday3987
text:
Selamat malam warga yang budiman. Izinkan saya menyampaikan beberapa apresiasi terhadap video spesial ini. Baik, langsung saja saya paparkan poin-poinnya
1. Terimakasih banyak atas video spesial anyone yang sangat spesial ini
2. Apresiasi tinggi untuk ketampanan, kesempurnaan body, talenta, dan segala yang ada pada diri member. Dengan catatan, semoga kami masih bisa (tetap) waras setelah menonton video ini. 
3. Pengaturan kamera yang sangat istimewa dan sangat keren. Beri applause, terimakasih direktur kamera dan kameramen. 
4. Konsep yang sangat menarik dan unik yang lagi-lagi membuat seventeen lain daripada yang lain. Ga pake mobil ga pake balapan aja udah racing di otak kami, tapi gapapa, kami terima dengan sangat lapang dada. Terimakasih PD-nim. 
5. Outfit yang fashionable abis, yang pastinya sukses membuat carat geger dan jejeritan. Terimakasih untuk tim stylish. 

Mungkin cukup sekian, karena sejujurnya saya sudah speechless dari awal. Saya harap apa yang saya paparkan belum cukup karena betapa berharganya seventeen dan banyaknya yang harus diapresiasi, terimakasih, selamat malam.
